author: daily.news4210
transcript: America, free to lay recalls potato chips over undeclared allergium. Now potato chips, so the FDA recently announced a limited recall of one of the most popular potato chips in the US due to an undeclared allergium. The recall affects certain 13 ounce bags of lays classic potato chips, according to free to lay statement published by the FDA on Monday. According to the officials, the bags may contain undeclared milk. Free to lay told fox business that 6,344 bags are affected by the recall. Now the products including this recall were distributed to certain retail stores and e-commerce distributors in Oregon and Washington. Consumers would have been able to purchase these chips as early as November 3rd, 2024. So free to lay urges consumers to check their 13 ounce lays classic potato chips bags for a guaranteed fresh date reading February 11th, 2025. Daily bags with that information should be discarded by consumers with milk allergies. Those with an allergy or severe sensitivity to milk run the risk of a serious or life-threatening allergic reaction if they consume the recalled product.

author: user529773907
transcript: Breaking news, a teddy bear covered in human skin was found outside of a gas station. Authorities in California say they were called to the area around 12.30pm on July 13th. This was after they were following up on a report of a quote object that appeared to be human remains. This was per written statement from the San Bernardino Sheriff's Office. Witnesses described the bear as having a face-like piece sewn onto its head, along with what appeared to be skin-like material stitched all over its body. Shortly after the call came through, authorities investigated and a corner came and removed the teddy bear. It was then taken away for further investigation. At this time, the teddy bear's origin has not yet been confirmed. However, a similar-looking teddy bear made with quote fake gore and labeled human skin bear was found listed on Etsy. That discovery led some to speculate that the incident may have been a staged art prank. As of Sunday afternoon, authorities have not verified the material or further released any details. In addition, at this time, the investigation is still ongoing. The gas station in which the teddy bear was located reopened to the public at approximately 2.15pm. To stay up to date on this case, make sure you click the playlist below. I'll keep you guys updated, what do you think? Drop in the comments.
